The Minister of Foreign Affairs, Geoffrey Onyeama has recovered from the coronavirus disease (COVID-19). The minister tested positive for the novel disease last month after a throat irritation. He took to his Twitter account yesterday to announce that  he has now tested negative after three weeks isolation. “I am eternally grateful to my family, the C-in-C and VP, the medical team, relations, friends, colleagues, religious leaders and numerous well-wishers, who through their care, prayers, fasting, messages of support and encouragement never let me walk alone,” he posted. A total of 47,290 cases of the coronavirus have been recorded in Nigeria since the first case was announced in late February. 33,609 have recovered, but 956 people have also died.